The paper presents a deep learning approach for segmenting rodent brain lesions on MRI scans, which falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a fully convolutional neural network (ConvNet) also suggests that the paper may be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves medical imaging, which could potentially place it under the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
